Topic: Virtual Environments & pip (Professional Python Setup)

📅 Date: 06 March 2026
⏱️ Duration: ~45 minutes

1️⃣ What is pip?

pip is Python’s package manager.

It allows you to install external libraries.

Example libraries:

numpy

pandas

flask

requests

tensorflow

Install a Package
pip install numpy

Check installed packages:

pip list

Upgrade a package:

pip install --upgrade numpy

Uninstall:

pip uninstall numpy
2️⃣ Why Virtual Environments?

Different projects need different versions of libraries.

Without virtual environments → conflicts happen.

Virtual environments create isolated Python environments.

3️⃣ Creating Virtual Environment

Inside your project folder:

python -m venv myenv

This creates a folder called myenv.

4️⃣ Activate Virtual Environment
Windows
myenv\Scripts\activate

You will see:

(myenv) C:\project>

Now packages install only inside this project.

5️⃣ Deactivate Environment
deactivate
6️⃣ Why Developers Use This

Virtual environments are used in:

Web development

Data science projects

AI/ML projects

Production software

🧠 Memory Trick

pip → install libraries

venv → isolate environment

activate → start environment

deactivate → exit

